L1 Questions (Beginner Level)

1Ô∏è‚É£ In Git, explain the push and pull commands.
    ‚Ä¢    git push uploads local repository content to a remote repository.
    ‚Ä¢    git pull fetches changes from a remote repository and merges them into the local branch.

2Ô∏è‚É£ What is the use of Git tags?
    ‚Ä¢    Git tags mark specific points in the repository‚Äôs history, often used for version releases (e.g., v1.0).

3Ô∏è‚É£ What are the different types of branches in Git?
    ‚Ä¢    Main/Master Branch: The production-ready branch.
    ‚Ä¢    Feature Branch: For developing new features.
    ‚Ä¢    Develop Branch: Integration branch for new features before merging into the main branch.
    ‚Ä¢    Release Branch: Prepares stable code for release.
    ‚Ä¢    Hotfix Branch: For urgent fixes in production.

4Ô∏è‚É£ How do you write an Ansible playbook, and what client requirements do you consider?
    ‚Ä¢    A playbook is a YAML file defining tasks to be executed on remote servers.
    ‚Ä¢    Considerations: OS compatibility, dependencies, idempotency, user permissions, and rollback strategies.

name: Install Nginx
hosts: webservers
become: yes
tasks:
name: Install Nginx
  apt: 
    name: nginx
    state: present

5Ô∏è‚É£ In Python, what are lists and tuples, and how do they differ?
    ‚Ä¢    Lists: Mutable, dynamic, and defined using [].
    ‚Ä¢    Tuples: Immutable, faster, and defined using ().

6Ô∏è‚É£ In CloudWatch, what is the use of log groups and log trails?
    ‚Ä¢    Log Groups: Logical containers for log streams from different services.
    ‚Ä¢    Log Trails: Capture and store API activity for auditing (linked with CloudTrail).

7Ô∏è‚É£ In Terraform, what is the purpose of init, plan, and apply commands?
    ‚Ä¢    terraform init ‚Üí Initializes the working directory.
    ‚Ä¢    terraform plan ‚Üí Shows what changes will be made.
    ‚Ä¢    terraform apply ‚Üí Applies the changes to the infrastructure.
8Ô∏è‚É£ What happens if the Terraform state file is accidentally deleted?
    ‚Ä¢    If stored locally, it‚Äôs lost, and manual intervention is needed.
    ‚Ä¢    If stored remotely (e.g., S3), it can be recovered from the backend.

9Ô∏è‚É£ What is the purpose of creating S3 bucket policies?
    ‚Ä¢    To define access permissions at the bucket level for users, groups, or AWS services.

üîü How do you maintain the lifecycle of an S3 bucket?
    ‚Ä¢    Implement lifecycle policies for transitions (e.g., move data to Glacier) and expiration (auto-delete old objects).

1Ô∏è‚É£1Ô∏è‚É£ In Airflow, if a job fails, how do you debug it?
    ‚Ä¢    Check logs (airflow logs <dag_id>), review task instance details, retry the job, or test tasks manually.

1Ô∏è‚É£2Ô∏è‚É£ If you‚Äôre facing performance issues on a server, how do you troubleshoot?
    ‚Ä¢    Check CPU (top), memory (free -m), disk (df -h), I/O (iostat), and logs (journalctl -xe)


L2 Questions (Advanced Level)

1Ô∏è‚É£ What are Network ACLs and Security Groups, and how do they differ?
    ‚Ä¢    Network ACLs: Stateless, applied at the subnet level, allow/deny specific traffic.
    ‚Ä¢    Security Groups: Stateful, applied at the instance level, allow only permitted traffic.

2Ô∏è‚É£ Explain EC2 instances and handling multiple VPCs.
    ‚Ä¢    EC2 instances are virtual servers in AWS. Multiple VPCs can be connected using VPC peering or Transit Gateway.

3Ô∏è‚É£ How do you configure AWS RDS, and what factors do you consider?
    ‚Ä¢    Factors: Instance size, storage type (GP2/IO1), backup retention, multi-AZ, read replicas, and security settings.

4Ô∏è‚É£ How much data is stored in your RDS MySQL?
    ‚Ä¢    Use SELECT table_schema AS DB, SUM(data_length + index_length) / 1024 / 1024 AS SIZE_MB FROM information_schema.tables GROUP BY table_schema;

5Ô∏è‚É£ How many masters and slaves are in RDS?
    ‚Ä¢    RDS uses one primary instance (master) and multiple replicas (read replicas for read scalability).
6Ô∏è‚É£ How do you configure a Grafana dashboard?
    ‚Ä¢    Add a data source (e.g., Prometheus, CloudWatch), create a panel, define metrics, and set visualization options.

7Ô∏è‚É£ What kind of CI/CD pipelines are you familiar with?
    ‚Ä¢    Jenkins, GitHub Actions, GitLab CI/CD, AWS CodePipeline, ArgoCD.

8Ô∏è‚É£ Explain Declarative vs. Scripting pipelines.
    ‚Ä¢    Declarative Pipelines: Define the pipeline as code using YAML or JSON (e.g., Jenkinsfile).
    ‚Ä¢    Scripting Pipelines: Use scripting (e.g., Bash, Python) to define steps dynamically.

9Ô∏è‚É£ In Kubernetes, if a pod is in a pending state, how do you troubleshoot?
    ‚Ä¢    Check pod status (kubectl get pods), describe pod (kubectl describe pod <pod-name>), check events (kubectl get events).

üîü If Docker containers are consuming too much disk space, how do you fix it?
    ‚Ä¢    Run docker system prune to clean unused containers, images, and volumes.

1Ô∏è‚É£1Ô∏è‚É£ In Linux, how do you attach and detach a filesystem?
    ‚Ä¢    Attach: mount /dev/sdX /mnt
    ‚Ä¢    Detach: umount /mnt

1Ô∏è‚É£2Ô∏è‚É£ How do you print the last 15 lines of a file in Linux?
    ‚Ä¢    tail -n 15 filename.txt

